The paper focuses on improving the performance of distributed computing clusters, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The proposed algorithm involves coding techniques, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses load allocation and budget constraints, which are topics in Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Control Systems (cs.SY), respectively. Finally, the experiments are conducted on Amazon EC2, which is a network infrastructure, making Networked Systems (cs.NI) another likely sub-category.
